@page
@model SailScores.Web.Pages.Help.IndexModel
@{
    Layout = "/Pages/Help/_HelpLayout.cshtml";
    ViewData["Title"] = "Help";
}

<h1 class="h2">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
<p>
    SailScores should be intuitive and easy to use without documentation.
    But if you're curious, troubleshooting, or want to dig deeper, these pages are here
    to support you.
</p>
<p>
    We’re actively expanding this section over the 2025–26 winter. If there’s
    something you’d like explained or clarified, we’d love to
    <a href="mailto:info@sailscores.com">hear from you.</a>
</p>
<p>
    Here's what you'll find:
</p>

<section id="getting-started">
    <a asp-page="/Help/GettingStarted"><h3>Getting Started</h3></a>
    <p>A step-by-step guide to setting up your club, creating series, and understanding the basics of how this site works.</p>
</section>

<section id="faq">
    <a asp-page="/Help/FAQ"><h3>FAQ</h3></a>
    <p>Quick answers to common questions about SailScores&mdash;perfect for new users or anyone needing a refresher.</p>
</section>

<section id="deep-dive">
    <h3>Reference &mdash; Coming Soon</h3>
    <p class="text-muted">
        Reference material, scoring notes, and technical guidance are being prepared
        and will be published during the 2025&ndash;26 winter. For now, the <a asp-page="/Help/Reference">Reference</a>
        page contains ideas for more coverage. If you need specific help sooner, please
        <a href="mailto:info@sailscores.com">contact us</a>.
    </p>
</section>
